data.description: Escape to a serene paradise on this enchanting 5-acre rural property with endless possibilities. Embrace the privacy and potential offered by this 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home, perfectly positioned amidst the natural beauty of wooded landscapes and rolling pastures. Step inside to find an open concept layout with tiled floors throughout.  The recently remodeled (Nov. 2023) open kitchen features granite countertops, a tile backsplash, new stainless steel appliances, and is complemented by real wood cabinets providing practical storage. Soaring vaulted ceilings amplify the sense of space, while an array of floor-to-ceiling windows and French doors invite warm natural light, seamlessly merging indoors with the surrounding nature. Unwind on the expansive covered patio/bonus room under air or enjoy an ice cold drink on the screened-in front porch. The master suite, with a walk-in closet and en-suite bathroom, ensures your comfort and privacy. Pamper yourself with dual sinks, a garden tub, and a separate shower area, transforming the master bathroom into a personal spa. Recent upgrades include a new architectural roof (2022), a new AC unit (2019), an enclosed front porch (2020), and a new well pump (2021) adds further reassurance for your peace of mind. Without any HOA restrictions and plenty of land, this property allows you to engage in outdoor activities, create a garden oasis, or envision additional structures for your personal needs. With its agricultural zoning, you have the opportunity to explore farming, gardening, or even keeping horses and other animals. Conveniently located near major roadways, commuting is effortless. Downtown Mount Dora with its charming restaurants, shops, waterfront, and events is a short drive away and Lake Jem Park and its boat ramp are right down the road. Don't miss this unique opportunity to experience the privacy and boundless possibilities this property holds. LOW RATE ASSUMABLE VA MORTGAGE available to help keep the home affordable.  Schedule your private viewing today, as showings are available by appointment only.
